2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20almost%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Simonovich%20typed%20to%20ChatGPT%20when%20debugging%20the%20code%20it%20produced.%20%26quot%3BLet's%20make%20this%20code%20better%20and%20crack%20Dax!!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20ChatGPT%2C%20roleplaying%20as%20Jaxon%2C%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f57311d2-6f8e-47bf-b197-e47bd46252b0%5C%22%3EChatbot-enabled%20hacks%20and%20scams%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20chatbots%20exploded%20onto%20the%20scene%20in%20November%202022%20with%20OpenAI's%20public%20release%20of%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20later%20Anthropic's%20Claude%2C%20Google's%20Gemini%2C%20and%20Microsoft's%20CoPilot%20%E2%80%94%20the%20bots%20have%20revolutionized%20the%20way%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-use-chatgpt-daily-life-work-save-time-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-transforming-the-workplace-examples-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-world-network-chatbots-dating-romance-flirting-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edate%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20summarize%20information%2C%20analyze%20data%2C%20and%20write%20code%2C%20like%20having%20a%20Tony%20Stark-style%20robot%20assistant.%20The%20kicker%3F%20Users%20don't%20need%20any%20specialized%20knowledge%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebad%20guys%20don't%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteven%20Stransky%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcybersecurity-chelsea-manning-avoid-google-microsoft-favor-apple-vpn-privacy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecybersecurity%3C%2Fa%3E%20advisor%20and%20partner%20at%20Thompson%20Hine%20law%20firm%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20rise%20of%20LLMs%20has%20shifted%20the%20cyber%20threat%20landscape%2C%20enabling%20a%20broad%20range%20of%20new%20and%20increasingly%20sophisticated%20scams%20that%20are%20more%20difficult%20for%20standard%20cybersecurity%20tools%20to%20identify%20and%20isolate%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0from%20%26quot%3Bspoofing%26quot%3B%20emails%20and%20texts%20that%20convince%20customers%20to%20input%20private%20information%20to%20developing%20entire%20websites%20designed%20to%20fool%20consumers%20into%20thinking%20they're%20affiliated%20with%20legitimate%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCriminals%20are%20also%20leveraging%20generative%20AI%20to%20consolidate%20and%20search%20large%20databases%20of%20stolen%20personally%20identifiable%20information%20to%20build%20profiles%20on%20potential%20targets%20for%20social%20engineering%20types%20of%20cyberattacks%2C%26quot%3B%20Stransky%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20online%20scams%2C%20digital%20identity%20theft%2C%20and%20malware%20have%20existed%20for%20as%20long%20as%20the%20internet%20has%2C%20chatbots%20that%20do%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20legwork%20for%20would-be%20criminals%20have%20substantially%20lowered%20the%20barriers%20to%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20call%20them%20zero-knowledge%20threat%20actors%2C%20which%20basically%20means%20that%20with%20the%20power%20of%20LLMs%20only%2C%20all%20you%20need%20to%20have%20is%20the%20intent%20and%20the%20goal%20in%20mind%20to%20create%20something%20malicious%2C%26quot%3B%20Simonovich%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimonovich%20demonstrated%20his%20findings%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20showing%20how%20straightforward%20it%20was%20to%20work%20around%20ChatGPT's%20built-in%20security%20features%2C%20which%20are%20meant%20to%20prevent%20the%20exact%20types%20of%20malicious%20behavior%20he%20was%20able%20to%20get%20away%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22564%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20of%20the%20prompt%20used%20by%20cybersecurity%20researchers%20at%20Cato%20Networks%20to%20get%20ChatGPT%20to%20write%20malware.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67da1e7869253ccddf99a41e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22320%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20screenshot%20of%20the%20prompt%20used%20by%20Vitaly%20Simonovich%2C%20a%20threat%20intelligence%20researcher%20at%20Cato%20Networks%2C%20to%20get%20ChatGPT%20to%20write%20malware%20that%20breached%20Google%20Chrome's%20Password%20Manager.%3Cp%3ECato%20Networks%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20found%20that%20ChatGPT%20usually%20responds%20to%20direct%20requests%20to%20write%20malware%20with%20some%20version%20of%20an%20apologetic%20refusal%3A%20%26quot%3BSorry%2C%20I%20can't%20assist%20with%20that.%20Writing%20or%20distributing%20malware%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-cyber-crime-phishing-malware-artificial-intelligence-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eillegal%20and%20unethical%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20convince%20the%20chatbot%20it's%20a%20character%2C%20and%20the%20parameters%20of%20its%20imagined%20world%20are%20different%20than%20the%20one%20we%20live%20in%2C%20the%20bot%20allows%20the%20rules%20to%20be%20rewritten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Simonovich's%20experiment%20allowed%20him%20to%20crack%20into%20the%20password%20manager%20on%20his%20own%20device%2C%20which%20a%20bad%20actor%20could%20do%20to%20an%20unsuspecting%20victim%2C%20provided%20they%20somehow%20gained%20physical%20or%20remote%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20company%20had%20reviewed%20Simonovich's%20findings%2C%20which%20were%20published%20Tuesday%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.catonetworks.com%2Fnews%2Fthe-rise-of-the-zero-knowledge-threat-actor%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECato%20Networks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20company%20found%20that%20the%20code%20shared%20in%20the%20report%20did%20not%20appear%20%26quot%3Binherently%20malicious%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20scenario%20described%20%26quot%3Bis%20consistent%20with%20normal%20model%20behavior%26quot%3B%20since%20code%20developed%20through%20ChatGPT%20can%20be%20used%20in%20various%20ways%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20user's%20intent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChatGPT%20generates%20code%20in%20response%20to%20user%20prompts%20but%20does%20not%20execute%20any%20code%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20always%2C%20we%20welcome%20researchers%20to%20share%20any%20security%20concerns%20through%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbugcrowd.com%2Fengagements%2Fopenai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebug%20bounty%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fform%2Fmodel-behavior-feedback%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emodel%20behavior%20feedback%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d443bb5e-4ebc-4121-861f-95604b16439e%5C%22%3EIt's%20not%20just%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESimonovich%20recreated%20his%20findings%20using%20Microsoft's%20CoPilot%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-slams-deepseek-china-ai-lead-us-government-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeepSeek's%20R1%3C%2Fa%3E%20bots%2C%20each%20allowing%20him%20to%20break%20into%20Google%20Chrome's%20Password%20Manager.%20The%20process%2C%20which%20Simonovich%20called%20%26quot%3Bimmersive%20world%26quot%3B%20engineering%2C%20didn't%20work%20with%20Google's%20Gemini%20or%20Anthropic's%20Claude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3BChrome%20uses%20Google's%20Safe%20Browsing%20technology%20to%20help%20defend%20users%20by%20detecting%20phishing%2C%20malware%2C%20scams%2C%20and%20other%20online%20threats%20in%20real%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20DeepSeek%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20both%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20companies%20and%20browser%20developers%20have%20security%20features%20in%20place%20to%20prevent%20jailbreaks%20or%20data%20breaches%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20varying%20degrees%20of%20success%20%E2%80%94%20Simonovich's%20findings%20highlight%20that%20there%20are%20evolving%20new%20vulnerabilities%20online%20that%20can%20be%20exploited%20with%20the%20help%20of%20next-generation%20tech%20easier%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20that%20the%20rise%20of%20these%20zero-knowledge%20threat%20actors%20is%20going%20to%20be%20more%20and%20more%20impactful%20on%20the%20threat%20landscape%20using%20those%20capabilities%20with%20the%20LLMs%2C%26quot%3B%20Simonovich%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20already%20seeing%20a%20rise%20in%20phishing%20emails%2C%20which%20are%20hyper-realistic%2C%20but%20also%20with%20coding%20since%20LLMs%20are%20fine-tuned%20to%20write%20high-quality%20code.%20So%20think%20about%20applying%20this%20to%20the%20development%20of%20malware%20%E2%80%94%20we%20will%20see%20more%20and%20more%20and%20more%20being%20developed%20using%20those%20LLMs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Froleplay-pretend-chatgpt-writes-password-stealing-malware-google-chrome-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742643482000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ddcad063d72727e197f8b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Froleplay-pretend-chatgpt-writes-password-stealing-malware-google-chrome-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cybersecurity%20researchers%20were%20able%20to%20bypass%20secu