nown%20in%20France%20and%20had%20%26quot%3Ba%20more%20feminine%20connotation%2C%26quot%3B%20Mandonnaud%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Flink.gale.com%2Fapps%2Fdoc%2FA14089263%2FITOF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWomen's%20Wear%20Daily%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%20However%2C%20the%20layout%20and%20aesthetics%20of%2038%20Sephora%20shops%20would%20change%20to%20match%20Shop%208's%2011%20boutiques.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20a%20more%20sophisticated%20look%20without%20plastic%20baskets%20and%20discount%20signs%2C%20Mandonnaud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20origins%20of%20the%20name%20Sephora%20are%20a%20bit%20mysterious.%20One%20theory%20is%20that%20it%20has%20Biblical%20connotations%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bustle.com%2Farticles%2F52509-the-most-unusual-baby-names-of-2014-what-do-they-mean%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBustle%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Zipporah%20was%20the%20name%20of%20Moses'%20wife%20in%20the%20Book%20of%20Exodus%2C%20but%20the%201956%20film%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ten%20Commandments%26quot%3B%20changed%20her%20name%20to%20Sephora.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESephora's%20flagship%20store%20opened%20on%20Paris's%20Champs-%C3%89lys%C3%A9es%20in%201996.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228034%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pedestrians%20walk%20by%20Sephora%20in%20Paris%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d1ed80585f1dff88b1f3db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225356%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESephora's%20flagship%20store%20on%20the%20Champs-%C3%89lys%C3%A9es%20in%20Paris%20in%202024.%3Cp%3EMIGUEL%20MEDINA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELocated%20on%20the%20popular%20street%2C%20perfect%20for%20drawing%20in%20tourists%2C%20the%2012%2C916-square-foot%20store%20was%20France's%20largest%20freestanding%20perfumery%20when%20it%20opened%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lvmh.com%2Fen%2Four-maisons%2Fselective-retailing%2Fsepho